Association of Bureaux De Change Operators of Nigeria (ABCON) has donated donated N10 million to the private sector led Coalition Against COVID-19 (CACOVID) Relief Fund and food items to 2,000 families  to support the pandemic fight nationwide. The association President, Aminu Gwadabe disclosed this while speaking at the donation of essential food items to the Destitute Home in Lagos. He said while the COVID-19 pandemic has impacted severely on the economy and the livelihood of millions of people across the world, it was also an opportunity to demonstrate love and support to the poor and vulnerable members of the society. Gwadabe explained that the association decided to focus its support on the poorest of the poor in the society by donating the food items to the most vulnerable families in the country. Dear valued readers, subscribe to the Daily Trust e-paper to continue enjoying our diet of authoritative news. Kindly subscribe here He said: “In Lagos we are donating food items to over 200 families through the Destitute Home, Yaba, and Lagos. The items include bags of rice, cartons of noodles and macaroni. “Similar donations were made by the ABCON zonal executives in Abuja, Kano, Kano State, Awka in Anambra State, Benin, Edo State, and Maduguri in Borno State.” “We have also taken measures to protect BDC operators and their customers from the coronavirus. For this purpose  ABCON  has  distributed over 20,000 face masks, hand sanitizers and infra-red thermometers to over 5,000 BDC members in all our cash disbursement centers across the country”, the forex expert added. COVID-19: ABCON supports CACOVID, 2000 families Kano gets N32m donation from Nestlé Nigeria COVID-19: Farmers donate palliatives worth millions to 6,000 poor